-- Chile Sees `Relatively' High Copper Price as Long as China Sustains Growth
-- B y   N a t h a n   C r o o k s
-- 2010-11-25T02:08:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-25/chile-sees-relatively-high-copper-price-as-long-as-china-sustains-growth.html
Chile, the world’s biggest copper
producer, expects “relatively” high prices for the metal used
in wiring and plumbing as long as Chinese demand continues to
grow. Chile’s Mining Minister Laurence Golborne made the
comments in an interview in Santiago.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nathan Crooks in Santiago at 
 ncrooks@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Attwood at 
 jattwood3@bloomberg.net  